Impaired teeth lead to percussion pain+~++, possible I movement. 4. Patients feel discomfort or pain when pressed on the apical position of the impaired tooth, there is no obvious swelling in the gum. 5. No response to the pulp vitality test, but premature permanent teeth or primary teeth&amp;#39;s inflamation could be spread to periapical areas before pulp necrosis, so patients could have response to the vitality test or even feel pain. 6. ailments.name: Acute suppurative periapical periodontitis

Patients feel severe spontaneous pain and percussion pain, teeth loosen a lot, neighbouring teeth could loosen in the later stage and patients could feel the pain possibly, the surrounding soft tissues also will have inflammation. There are three clinical stages: 1)Apical abscess: impaired teeth bring spontaneous and continuous pain severely, percussion(++)~(+++), movement II~III, apical areas flushes and patients feel light pain if touched. 2) Abscess under periosteum: usually the impaired condition has been around 5 days , patients feel extreme pain, affecting sleep and eating: a. impaired teeth bring extreme continuous and pulsating pain, patients feel the impaired teeth are detached and loosened further, light touch of the impaired teeth could cause unbearable pain; b. Percussion pain(+++), movement II~III, apical areas flush and swell, patients feel pain if touched; c. Regional lymph nodes swell, patients feel pain if touched; lower jaw molars have mouth opening limitation, serious cases could involve relevant maxillofacial cellulitis; d. patients feel aches and pains all over the body, body temperature rises(usually lower than 38), white blood cell number increases. 3) Abscess under mucosa: impaired teeth bring less pain, mucosa around apical areas pop out in hemisphere, gums feel tender for palpation check, the whole body&amp;#39;s discomfort fades away a bit. 2. Deep cavity, filled materials, and other hard tissue diseases are visible in the impaired teeth, crown shades change and deep periodontal pockets appear, etc. 3. X-ray inspection shows that lamina dura disappears, periodontal membrane space widens, possible bone mineral density decreases, or no obvious change. If it is chronic periapical periodontitis patient, grey area of bone desctruction could be found in the X-ray check film

plans.notes: Incise and drain and extract in the later period 3. Take antibacteria drugs a

ailments.name: Tongue licking habit
ailments.notes: The tongue licking habit is caused by the common use of the tongue to lick gaps in the dental arch, remnants of crowns and roots. When licking the upper front teeth, it causes the upper front teeth to tilt towards the lip, resulting in deep overlap and overlap of the front teeth; when licking the lower front teeth, it causes the lower front teeth to protrude forward, resulting in anticlinal teeth; if the upper and lower front teeth are licked at the same time, it causes the upper and lower front teeth to protrude forward, or it causes the double arch to protrude forward (commonly known as "whistling teeth"). The tongue is placed between the upper and lower front teeth during tongue licking. The pressure of the lingual muscles inhibits the growth of the upper anterior teeth, resulting in an open dentition with a pivot-shaped opening in the anterior region.

plans.notes: Correcting bad habits: teaching the correct way to move the tongue

The long-term effect can make the upper jaw protrude and the upper front teeth tilt labially, causing an abnormal relationship between the upper and lower jaws; protrusion of the lower jaw and inward tilt of the upper front teeth: biting the upper lip causes the lower jaw to protrude and the upper teeth to crowd and tilt towards the lingual side

ailments.notes: Espao bvio entre os dentes.

ailments.name: Alinhamento dos dentes - Mordida cruzada
ailments.notes: Pode ser dividida em mordida cruzada de um nico dente e mordida cruzada de vrios dentes. A mordida cruzada  uma condio dentria que afeta o alinhamento dos dentes. O principal sinal de mordida cruzada  que os dentes superiores se encaixam atrs dos dentes inferiores quando a boca est fechada ou em repouso.

plans.notes: Soluo:Aparelho ortodntico removvel, alinhadores invisveis ou aparelho ortodntico fixo podem ser utilizados para tratamento.
Soluo:A disposio dos dentes est relacionada a mltiplos fatores como gentica e hbitos orais. Recomenda-se manter bons hbitos de higiene oral e realizar inspees bucais regulares.

ailments.name: Alinhamento dos dentes - Mordida aberta
ailments.notes: A mordida aberta  um tipo de m ocluso caracterizada principalmente por espaamento vertical. Esse espaamento geralmente  visvel quando os dentes das duas arcadas esto completamente em contato.

plans.notes: Soluo:Aparelho ortodntico removvel, alinhadores invisveis ou aparelho ortodntico fixo podem ser utilizados para tratamento.

ailments.name: Alinhamento dos dentes - Mordida Cruzada
ailments.notes: Uma mordida cruzada  definida como deslocamento bucal de um dente posterior superior com ou sem contato entre a superfcie lingual da cspide lingual maxilar e a superfcie vestibular da cspide bucal do antagonista mandibular.

plans.notes: Soluo:Aparelho ortodntico removvel, alinhadores invisveis ou aparelho ortodntico fixo podem ser utilizados para tratamento.

ailments.name: Alinhamento dos dentes - Sobremordida
ailments.notes: Consulte a extenso da sobreposio vertical (superior-inferior) dos incisivos centrais superiores sobre os incisivos centrais inferiores,  uma sobremordida se a distncia for superior a 2-3 mm.

plans.notes: Soluo:Aparelho ortodntico removvel, alinhadores invisveis ou aparelho ortodntico fixo podem ser utilizados para tratamento.

ailments.name: Alinhamento de dentes-Overjet
ailments.notes: Overjet  a extenso da sobreposio horizontal (anterior-posterior) dos incisivos centrais superiores sobre os incisivos centrais inferiores;  overjet se for a superior a 2-3 mm.

plans.notes: Soluo:Aparelho ortodntico removvel, alinhadores invisveis ou aparelho ortodntico fixo podem ser utilizados para tratamento.

sicknesss.name: Alinhamento dos dentes
sicknesss.notes: A dentio normal tem aparncia regular e organizada, cada dente tem sua posio especfica no osso alveolar e os dentes so adjacentes uns aos outros; a disposio anormal dos dentes afetar a aparncia facial, a mastigao, a pronncia e outras funes.

sicknesss.notes: A placa dentria calcificada e os depsitos moles na superfcie dos dentes podem ter uma aparncia branco-amarelada a preto-acastanhada.
